<MainLayout 
  title="EICR Certificate in Croydon - Landlord Electrical Safety Certificates"
  description="Certified EICR testing and electrical safety certificates in Croydon. Landlord compliance, 18th Edition standards. Fast, reliable reports with same-day booking available."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl lg:py-28 lg:px-6">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-medium mb-6 leading-tight">
          EICR Certificate in Croydon - Landlord Electrical Safety Certificates
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg mb-8">
          EICR Certificate: Certified Electrical Installation Condition Reports for Homes & Landlords
          <br/><br/>
          If you're a landlord, homeowner, or business in Croydon, you must ensure your electrical systems are safe and compliant. Landlords, homeowners, and business operators are legally responsible for meeting electrical safety obligations in their properties. CR9 Electricians provides fast, certified EICR testing and reports that meet UK regulations — including the 18th Edition Wiring Standards. Only a competent electrician should carry out these inspections to ensure all safety standards are properly met.
        </p>
        <a href="#contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-green text-white rounded-2xl font-medium text-lg hover:bg-dark hover:text-white transition-all">
          Book EICR Inspection — 020 3519 9989
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="[content-visibility:auto] [contain-intrinsic-size:400px] relative">
        <div class="bg-green rounded-[45px] p-1 md:p-2 relative z-10">
          <Image src={seoImg} alt="EICR Certificate in Croydon" class="w-full h-auto rounded-[35px]" />
        </div>
        <div class="absolute top-8 left-8 right-8 bottom-8 bg-dark rounded-[45px] -z-10"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IMPORTANCE OF ELECTRICAL INSTALLATION CERTIFICATES -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Importance of Electrical Installation Certificates</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Electrical Installation Certificates (EICs) play a vital role in ensuring the safety and compliance of electrical installations within any property. Issued only after a thorough inspection and testing by a qualified electrician, these certificates confirm that the electrical system meets the latest electrical safety standards.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        For landlords in the private rented sector, holding valid electrical installation certificates is not just best practice—it's a legal requirement. EICs help identify potential electrical hazards before they become serious issues, reducing the risk of electrical fires and safeguarding both property and occupants.
      </p>
      <p>
        In rental properties, an EIC demonstrates a landlord's commitment to providing a safe living environment, while also offering peace of mind to tenants. By maintaining up-to-date electrical installation certificates, property owners can ensure their electrical installations are compliant, reliable, and less likely to cause costly or dangerous problems in the future.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PURPOSE OF EICR INSPECTIONS -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <Image src={seoImg} alt="EICR Inspection Process" class="rounded-[35px]" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Purpose of EICR Inspections</h2>
        <p class="mb-6">
          The main goal of an Electrical Installation Condition Report (EICR) inspection is to thoroughly assess the safety and integrity of a property's electrical installation. During an EICR inspection, a qualified electrician will carry out a detailed visual inspection and a series of tests on the electrical system, including the fuse board, circuit breakers, light fittings, and other electrical equipment.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          This process checks for signs of wear, damage, or deterioration, and ensures that all components comply with current regulations and safety standards. The installation condition report (EICR) provides a clear overview of the state of the electrical system, highlighting any defects, potential hazards, or areas where the installation falls short of required standards.
        </p>
        <p>
          The report also includes recommendations for repairs or upgrades, helping property owners and landlords maintain safe and compliant electrical installations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS AN EICR CERTIFICATE -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">What Is an EICR Certificate?</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        An EICR (Electrical Installation Condition Report) is a formal electrical inspection and test of the property's electrical systems. This electrical inspection identifies electrical faults, deterioration, defects, or non-compliance with current regulations and provides a coded summary of required remedial work.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-medium">
        EICRs are now a legal requirement for landlords in England every 5 years or at the start of a new tenancy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE CHECK DURING AN EICR -->
