          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <svg class="mr-2 w-5 h-5 mt-1 text-green">
              <use href="#icon-check"></use>
            </svg>
            <span>Inspection of outdoor electrical equipment, such as exterior lighting and sockets</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ACTIONS LISTED IN THE REPORT -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">Actions Listed in the Report</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        An EICR report provides a detailed list of actions required to bring the electrical installation up to current regulations and safety standards. These actions may involve repairing or replacing faulty electrical equipment, upgrading outdated components, or making modifications to the existing installation.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Each action is classified using a coding system to indicate its urgency and importance. For example, a C1 code signals that the installation is immediately dangerous and requires urgent attention, while a C2 code highlights potentially dangerous issues that should be addressed as soon as possible. Less urgent recommendations are marked as C3, indicating that improvements are advised but not essential for immediate safety.
      </p>
      <p>
        Addressing the actions listed in the EICR report promptly is crucial to ensure the electrical installation remains safe and compliant, and to avoid the risks associated with unsafe or non-compliant electrical systems.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LEGAL COMPLIANCE -->
