  <!-- HOW SOON TO CORRECT ISSUES -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-6">How Soon Should I Correct Any Electrical Issues</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Electrical issues identified during an EICR inspection should be resolved without delay to protect the safety of everyone in the property. According to UK law, any urgent remedial work highlighted in the report must be completed within 28 days of the inspection date—or sooner if specified by the electrician.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Once the work is finished, written confirmation should be provided to all relevant parties, including the landlord, tenants, and the local housing authority. Ignoring or delaying necessary repairs can lead to legal penalties, fines, or even prosecution.
      </p>
      <p>
        In cases where the electrical installation is found to be immediately dangerous, the electrician may recommend shutting down the affected circuits or the entire system until urgent remedial work is completed. Prompt action ensures compliance with safety standards and helps prevent accidents or further damage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

